@layout DocLayout
@page "/docs/app/stat-card"

<PageTitle>Stat Card - Tazor</PageTitle>

<PageHead>
    <Title>Stat Card</Title>
</PageHead>

<Lead>
    The Statistics Card, or StatCard, component provides a consistent way to elevate key metrics
    in the page. Each portion of the card is supported by a <code>RenderFragment</code>, so you
    are free to throw any sort of content at it that will fit. Similarly, the Additional Data and Note
    fragments are completely optional.
</Lead>

<SubHeader>Basic Usage</SubHeader>

<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
    <StatCard>
        <Title>
            @HeroIcons.ChartPie("inline-block")
            <span>Total Revenue</span>
        </Title>
        <AdditionalData>
            <div>
                <Badge Type="BadgeType.Success">
                    @HeroIcons.ArrowUpRight("inline-block", "w-4 h-4")
                    <span>23%</span>
                </Badge>
            </div>
        </AdditionalData>
        <Statistic>
            $437,892
        </Statistic>
    </StatCard>

    <StatCard>
        <Title>
            @HeroIcons.ChartPie("inline-block")
            <span>Retail Sentiment</span>
        </Title>
        <AdditionalData>
            <div>
                <Badge Type="BadgeType.Error">
                    @HeroIcons.ArrowDownRight("inline-block", "w-4 h-4")
                    <span>3.25%</span>
                </Badge>
            </div>
        </AdditionalData>
        <Statistic>
            $123,456
        </Statistic>
        <Note>
            <div class="text-sm">
                Source: <a href="#">tazor.org</a>
            </div>
        </Note>
    </StatCard>

    <StatCard>
        <Title>
            <span>Simple Metric</span>
        </Title>
        <Statistic>
            Hello, World
        </Statistic>
    </StatCard>
</div>

<CodeBlock Code="@Resources.Examples_App_StatCard" Language="razor" />